{"title_page": "Fritz Kiersch", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Fritz Kiersch\n| birth_name    = George Keith Kiersch\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1951|7|23}}\n| birth_place   = [[Alpine, Texas]], U.S.\n| occupation    = [[Film director]], [[screenwriter]]\n}}\n\n'''George Keith \"Fritz\" Kiersch''' (born July 23, 1951 in [[Alpine, Texas]]) is an American film director,<ref name=NYT1>{{cite web |work=[[The New York Times]] |title='TUFF TURF,' IN LOS ANGELES |authorlink=Janet Maslin |author=Maslin, Janet |date=February 1, 1985 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/02/01/movies/tuff-turf-in-los-angeles.html}}</ref> writer and producer.<ref name=NYT>{{cite web |work=[[The New York Times]] |title=Into the Sun (1992) Review/Film; Spoofing Movie Stars And a War |first=Janet |last=Maslin |authorlink=Janet Maslin |date=January 31, 1992 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9E0CE7D7133AF932A05752C0A964958260}}</ref> He is perhaps best known for directing the horror film ''[[Children of the Corn (1984 film)|Children of the Corn]]'' and the drama ''[[Tuff Turf]]''.<ref>Collings, Michael R., ''The films of Stephen King'', (Wildside Press, 2006), 170.</ref> Currently, Kiersch is the head of [[Point Park University]]'s Cinema Arts Program.<ref>[http://www2.okcu.edu/movingarts/#faculty Okcu.edu]</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Director ===\n* 1984 ''[[Children of the Corn (1984 film)|Children of the Corn]]''\n* 1985 ''[[Tuff Turf]]''\n* 1987 ''[[Winners Take All (film)|Winners Take All]]''\n* 1987 ''[[Gor (film)|Gor]]''\n* 1989 ''[[Under the Boardwalk (film)|Under the Boardwalk]]''\n* 1990 ''[[Fatal Charm (1990 film)|Fatal Charm]]'' (video) (as [[Alan Smithee]])\n* 1990 ''[[Swamp Thing (1990 TV series)|Swamp Thing]]'' (TV series)\n* 1992 ''[[Into the Sun (1992 film)|Into the Sun]]''\n* 1994 ''Shattered Image'' (TV movie)\n* 1995 ''[[The Stranger (1995 film)|The Stranger]]''\n* 1997 ''Crayola Kids Adventures: Tales of Gulliver's Travels'' (video)\n* 2006 ''[[Surveillance (2006 film)|Surveillance]]''\n* 2006 ''[[The Hunt (2006 film)|The Hunt]]''\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0452607}}\n\n{{Fritz Kiersch}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kiersch, Fritz}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Alpine, Texas]]\n[[Category:Film producers from Texas]]\n[[Category:American male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:English-language film directors]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Texas]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from Texas]]\n\n\n{{US-film-director-1950s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Fritz Kiersch\n| birth_name    = George Keith Kiersch\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1951|7|23}}\n| birth_place   = [[Alpine, Texas]], U.S.\n| occupation    = [[Film director]], [[screenwriter]]\n}}\n\n'''George Keith \"Fritz\" Kiersch''' (born July 23, 1951 in [[Alpine, Texas]]) is an American film director,<ref name=NYT1>{{cite web |work=[[The New York Times]] |title='TUFF TURF,' IN LOS ANGELES |authorlink=Janet Maslin |author=Maslin, Janet |date=February 1, 1985 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/02/01/movies/tuff-turf-in-los-angeles.html}}</ref> writer and producer.<ref name=NYT>{{cite web |work=[[The New York Times]] |title=Into the Sun (1992) Review/Film; Spoofing Movie Stars And a War |first=Janet |last=Maslin |authorlink=Janet Maslin |date=January 31, 1992 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9E0CE7D7133AF932A05752C0A964958260}}</ref> He is perhaps best known for directing the horror film ''[[Children of the Corn (1984 film)|Children of the Corn]]'' and the drama ''[[Tuff Turf]]''.<ref>Collings, Michael R., ''The films of Stephen King'', (Wildside Press, 2006), 170.</ref> Currently, Kiersch is the head of [[Point Park University]]'s Cinema Arts Program.<ref>[http://www2.okcu.edu/movingarts/#faculty Okcu.edu]</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Director ===\n* 1984 ''[[Children of the Corn (1984 film)|Children of